xinequery
------------------------------------------
Xinequery is a small command-line program that displays information about
Xinerama screens on an X11 display. It is written in C and depends on the
Xinerama library. Released under the Unlicense.

A typical use would be to quickly get the screen dimensions and origin points
for all your Xinerama screens, to help yourself pick the location for a window
that opens automatically. (For example, a conky display.) Xinequery also
provides a convenient procedure called grab mode, which returns the absolute
and relative coordinates of any point on the display after you click on it.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.14-2
  libX11_6-1.4.4-1
  libXinerama1-1.1.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-10-1
  automake-4-10
  binutils-2.22.51-2
  cygport-0.10.10-1
  gawk-4.0.1-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  https://frigidcode.com/code/xinequery/

Canonical download:
  https://frigidcode.com/code/xinequery/xinequery-0.4.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack xinequery-0.4.3-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./xinequery-0.4.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/xinequery-0.4.3-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/xinequery-0.4.3-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(xinequery)
  /usr/bin/xinequery.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/xinequery.README
  /usr/share/doc/xinequery/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/xinequery/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/xinequery/DONATE
